1. WHAT IS COMPREHENSION? THE BIG PICTURE
Definition
The word Comprehension comes from the Latin comprehendere meaning to grasp fully. In an
examination context, comprehension is the ability to read a passage of text carefully and then answer
questions based strictly on what is written in that passage.
n NOTE: In UGC NET Paper 1, the passage is always given — you do NOT need prior subject
knowledge. Every answer is hidden inside the passage itself.
Why is Comprehension in Paper 1?
A university teacher or researcher must regularly read research papers, policy documents, reports and
books, then extract meaning, evaluate arguments and communicate ideas clearly. Comprehension tests
exactly these real-life skills.
