8. FINDING MAIN IDEA & THEME
What is the Main Idea?
The main idea is the central message of the entire passage — the one big point the author wants to
communicate. It is NOT a small detail or a single supporting example. It must cover the whole
passage, not just one paragraph.
How to Identify the Main Idea — Decision Tree
Q1: Does the first sentence state a clear general idea?
® YES ® That is likely the main idea (verify with the rest of the passage)
® NO ® Continue to Q2
Q2: Does the last sentence summarise the passage?
® YES ® That is likely the main idea
® NO ® Continue to Q3
Q3: What do ALL paragraphs have in common?
® The common thread across all paragraphs = the main idea
® Write it in one sentence and match to MCQ options
